Here, a complication arises, namely that the series on the right is not always convergent, so for example, the sequence made up of only ones, formula_37 will have an infinite formula_8-norm for formula_39 The space formula_40 is then defined as the set of all infinite sequences of real (or complex) numbers such that the formula_8-norm is finite.

One can check that as formula_8 increases, the set formula_40 grows larger. For example, the sequence
