Quotient vector space

Like every seminorm, the seminorm formula_152 induces a norm (defined shortly) on the canonical quotient vector space of formula_93 by its vector subspace 
formula_195
This normed quotient space is called and it is the subject of this article. We begin by defining the quotient vector space.

Given any formula_196 the coset formula_197 consists of all measurable functions formula_102 that are equal to formula_94 almost everywhere. 
The set of all cosets, typically denoted by 
