forms a vector space with origin formula_201 when vector addition and scalar multiplication are defined by formula_202 and formula_203 
This particular quotient vector space will be denoted by
formula_204
Two cosets are equal formula_205 if and only if formula_206 (or equivalently, formula_207), which happens if and only if formula_208 almost everywhere; if this is the case then formula_94 and formula_102 are identified in the quotient space. Hence, strictly speaking formula_211 consists of equivalence classes of functions.

