#formula_431 if and only if formula_95 does not contain sets of non-zero but arbitrarily small measure (e.g. the counting measure).

Neither condition holds for the Lebesgue measure on the real line while both conditions holds for the counting measure on any finite set. As a consequence of the closed graph theorem, the embedding is continuous, i.e., the identity operator is a bounded linear map from formula_433 to formula_11 in the first case and formula_11 to formula_433 in the second. Indeed, if the domain formula_95 has finite measure, one can make the following explicit calculation using Hölder&#x27;s inequality
